        <body>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Whereon the stagnatic of Business will deprive many<lb/> of their
                usual means of living, and whereas the existing<lb/> charitable societies have not
                the means active actual or pers-<lb/>pective to meet the demands to be made on them,
                therefore</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Resolved that the Israelites of <placeName>Phila<hi rend="sup"
                        >a</hi></placeName> from themselves<lb/> into a general relief association:
                    <del>as follows, of</del> for alleviating <del>distr</del><lb/> existing
                distress and aiding the existing societies as follows.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Resolved that the officers of the society be a president, &amp;<lb/>
                President Treasurer &amp; Secretary, and executive committee of <del>five</del>
                six</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Resolved that the city be divided into seven 7 districts &amp; a
                    coun<hi rend="sup">l</hi> be app<hi rend="sup">d</hi> to canvass<lb/> the city
                for subscriptions &amp; donations; said districts committees to<lb/> consist of five
                5 each, who also are to be a spending committee who<lb/> are to receive all the
                applicants for relief &amp; through them all<lb/> applications of relief are to be
                made. A recommendation of two will be enough.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Resolved. That a central station may be procured at <add>?</add> all
                can<lb/> apply for aid, and where articles for relief are to be kept.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Resolved that a person e engaged by the 13 C of officers to take
                charge of the<lb/> stores.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Resolved. That the executive committee and officers<lb/> meet three
                3 times per week, till otherwise ordered by the<lb/> whole committee</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Resolved All other societies may apply for and to the<lb/> Executive
                committee, <del>who will <add>?</add> to them a proportion-<lb/>ate part of funds
                    not needed by them.</del></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">That this <sic>organisation</sic> be dissolved on the <date>first
                    Monday<lb/> of the Passover</date></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">That any surplus funds be distributed by the Officers among<lb/> the
                existing charitable societies</p>
        </body>
